sentences: Monica Cosachov (born 7 September 1946) is an Argentine harpsichordist, pianist and composer.

She is currently Director of the Escuela Interdisciplinaria de Música (the Interdisciplinary School of Music), training center and artistic and social projects, work for which she won the Alicia Moreau de Justo prize for creative work and for supporting young artists.
In 2005 she was named director of the Fondo Nacional de las Artes (National Endowment for the Arts).
In 2002 she released the CD Bach De Buenos Aires and recently, her latest production, Mi Corazón es mi casa.
